snippet.title: An Eames Primer
snippet.description: The first book to capture the philosophy and spirit behind the work of Charles and Ray Eames, An Eames Primer offers an in-depth look at the couple's prolific legacy--one that has placed them among the most important American designers of the twentieth century. Those who know one or two aspects of the Eameses' work are often surprised to learn just how far and vast their range extended. Yet throughout their myriad works, from architecture and furniture to exhibition and design and ...

snippet.title: Exact two-point resistance, and the simple random walk on the complete graph minus edges
snippet.description: An analytical approach is developed to obtain the exact expressions for the two-point resistance, and the total effective resistance of the complete graph minus N edges of the opposite vertices. These expressions are written in terms of certain numbers that we introduced which we call the Bejaia and the Pisa numbers, these numbers are the natural generalizations of the bisected Fibonacci and Lucas numbers. The correspondence between random walks and the resistor networks is then used to obtain the exact expressions ...
